document.title: Tennessee Academic Standards for Fine Arts

B362DB9832664FDA8EA63548385CFA52.description:
Analyze dances from several genres, styles, historical time
periods, and/or world dance forms. Discuss how dance movement
characteristics, techniques, and artistic criteria relate to the ideas and
perspectives of the people from which the dance originates, and how the
analysis has expanded one's dance literacy.

69048EE694DA460C91AE356C95C33C6F.description:
Analyze dances from different genres, styles, historicaltime
periods, and/or world dance forms. Discuss how dance movement
characteristics, techniques, and artistic criteria relate to the ideas and
perspectives of the people from which the dance originates.

1CF9BDA40CFD4F03979BFF4C763BBF49.description:
Analyze and discuss dances from selected genres, styles,
and/or historical time periods, and formulate reasons for the similarities and
differences between them in relation to the ideas and perspectives of the
people from which the dances originate.

EFA3FED1E70F45959BE68B70091B6B4C.description:
Compare and contrast differences in dance expression
throughout the world. Analyze expressive movement in rituals and the
connection to present day dance.

124E4B2A6E8346EF920BA69A738EA568.description: Relate artistic ideas and works with societal, cultural, and historical text.

6A7A279615FE4114BD646D547FFA5168.description: Employ proper safety measures in the studio and theater.

BE2BFA9699204E58BC1763C4E0731410.description:
Consistently demonstrate proper safety measures in the dance
studio and theater while setting an example for peers.

7D881A4B12DA422E8AE0DFC63A1E482F.description:
Consistently demonstrate proper safety measures in the dance
studio and theater.

05547975CAB54F3D94885F9F20EA6601.description:
Demonstrate proper safety measures in the dance studio and
theater.

E91E682A397B41B594FEBBA6C690E8F9.description:
Understand how anatomy, physiology, and kinesiology relate to
dance.

91E5A6B037B04B6AA4513F0E61E3D59D.description:
Research physics concepts and/or muscles and skeletal
structures used in movement. Apply findings to improve technical ability in
dance technique.

2B80AADDE7E34FE0ACE3A126E50E590A.description:
Research specified muscles and skeletal structures used in
dance technique and apply principles of anatomy, physiology, andkinesiology
to dance.

FD3032EA06894B3DA647323292279FAA.description:
Understand how anatomy, physiology, and kinesiology relate to
dance.

C0138AFD56844E81BDFEDC15C6D10E67.description:
Create or analyze an existing dance phrase that is related to
content learned in another art area or academic subject. Identify principles of
other subjects as they occur in dance.

F6EC8B2AD3B142139D457733CDA8A0D4.description:
Review original choreography developed over time with
respect to its content and context and its relationship to personal
experiences. Reflect upon and analyze the components that contributed to
changes in one's personal growth.

E5A409BB43CC4C69BD20D2246948A149.description:
Analyze a piece of original choreography that is related to
content learned in other subject areas, and research its context. Synthesize
information learned, and share new ideas about its relationship to one's
perspective.

54168408DBB248E9964BCA81053A6F99.description:
Analyze a dance to determine the ideas expressed by the
choreographer. Explain how the perspectives expressed by the
choreographer may impact one's own interpretation. Determine whether or
not this dance can relate to personal experiences, technology, or other
academic subjects.

BFD8A29A01A44F6D837E66824645DF9C.description:
Analyze and compare various movement qualities and dance
elements from various genres and cross-cultural dances to one's own
personal experiences and knowledge.

932214C3B3064EABBBF6EB172FD00E85.description: Synthesize and relate knowledge and personal experiences to artistic endeavors.

577CDE35F4E94602B281DFC6896B3F35.description:
Define personal artistic preferences to critique dance. Consider
societal and personal values, a range of artistic expression, and importance
of technical proficiency. Justify views.

57E255CC8DC3453B89436EAF19C3FE8D.description:
Compare two or more dances using artistic criteria to evaluate
artistic expression and/or technical proficiency. Consider societal values and
a range of perspectives. Use genre-specific terminology.

EF3E53745399483492D48A72EB73A8DB.description:
Analyze the artistic expression of a dance. Discuss insights
using evaluative criteria and dance terminology.

657D5181BA2A45AABA2C6BD60187ED56.description:
Identify criteria for evaluating dance for different styles, genres,
and cultures. Use appropriate dance terminology.

5124B43FA5A1415385BCCC25771FF36A.description: Apply criteria to evaluate artistic work.

882DAF186DD04B43854FEF1A96FF26E7.description:
Analyze and interpret how the elements of dance, executionof
dance movement principles, and context contribute to artistic expression
across different genres, styles, or cultural movement practices. Use genrespecific terminology.

E7C7BB760140409AB065D9C512F9A5E4.description:
Analyze and discuss how the elements of dance, execution of
dance movement principles, and context contribute to artistic expression.Use
genre-specific terminology.

2AF24DC24AC64B149BB6B037A9B715CA.description:
Compare different dances, and discuss their intent and artistic
expression. Explain how the relationships among the components of dance
enhance meaning and support intent using genre-specificterminology.

906C46E77F8E4109ACCD24971E7C9480.description:
Identify and discuss the artistic expression in a dance or dance
phrase.

0F79050471C24ED080609AEF8F441F13.description: Interpret intent and meaning in artistic work.

8D60409CD0584B0A96F14CFA4305A1A4.description:
Construct a formal written critique of a student and/or
professional performance including all aspects of thepresentation.

B01D04E4FED34751AF435299B8EE6E6A.description:
Construct a formal written critique of a student orprofessional
performance.

DA3C6190D426469E96CE94F53AEA6427.description: Compare and analyze student or professional performances.

CBB79B2C33D24ECEA7BC72AE2E12BDDD.description:
Identify the elements of a dance critique, and apply to a
performance.

0A78E6362FE94A738771BE6A534D381F.description:
Generate appropriate feedback in verbal or written form for
peers and self to develop technique and performance skills. Analyze and
apply feedback from teachers, peers, or self-evaluation.

CA809FEE996046AFB240AA8B72D7E4BD.description:
Generate appropriate feedback in verbal or written form for
peers and self to develop technique and performance skills. Analyze and
apply feedback from teachers, peers, or self-evaluation.

27E01BAD5FFA4D08AC6D6BD50DE2A25B.description:
Generate appropriate feedback in verbal or written form for
peers and self to develop technique and performance skills. Analyze and
apply feedback from teachers, peers, or self-evaluation.

67482DF8D99B42CF95C0EB2CEAE3E761.description:
Generate appropriate feedback in verbal or written form for
peers and self to develop technique and performance skills. Analyze and
apply feedback from teachers, peers, or self-evaluation.

879664C165EF45CEA319F3594C97B099.description:
Explain how dance communicates aesthetic and/or cultural
values in a variety of genres, styles, or cultural movement practices. Use
genre-specific terminology.

5BF9941A0C2146B88BFDA90A45904C9E.description:
Analyze and compare the movement patterns and their
relationships in a variety of genres, styles, or cultural movement practices,
and explain how their differences impact structure, communication, and intent
within a cultural context. Use genre-specific terminology.

38D845558A1C4966BFE23422345B834F.description:
Analyze the use of elements of dance in a variety of genres,
styles, or cultural movement practices within a cultural context to
communicate intent. Use genre-specific terminology.

41F661C05B8D4178BB266C5B75A934AF.description:
Analyze original movement phrases identifying the elementsof
dance to solve given problems.

2BAA2A35ED5E487FBCDD0D2AE3D9E91B.description:
Apply recognized systems of dance documentation or symbol
systems to analyze and evaluate the artistry of a dance, and apply findings to
refine during the creative process.

79C495CA1F9049388B1FE250506777A7.description:
Apply recognized systems of dance documentation or symbol
systems to analyze and evaluate the artistry of a dance, and apply findings to
refine during the creative process.

8056F6AC8FC743148A019EB55991F012.description:
Document a dance as a tool to refine work during the creative
process.

2AAFD23599584DBAB807C4DD3619BA92.description:
Investigate a recognized system to document a dance
sequence by using words, symbols, or media technologies in order to refine
or complete artistic work.

0171DA3A399948F9AB43D29CCDEF9692.description:
Refine the artistic intent of a dance by manipulating
choreographic devices, dance structures/forms, and artistic criteria using selfreflection and feedback from others. Document choices made in therevision
process, and justify how the refinements support artistic intent.

0834E54329C24ECAB73BC50C3BC84A08.description:
Refine the artistic intent of a dance by manipulating
choreographic devices, dance structures/forms, and artistic criteria using selfreflection and feedback from others. Document choices made in the revision
process, and justify how the refinements support artistic intent.

8741C8AC3E6A426F8326ECB745F89F27.description:
Clarify the artistic intent of a dance by refining choreographic
processes and dance structures/forms, using established artistic criteria, selfreflection, and the feedback of others. Analyze and evaluate impact of
choices made in the revision process.

2A9AC132C2F441019A1DD118C39395E8.description:
Identify the artistic intent of a dance study by manipulating
choreographic devices and dance structures/forms based on established
artistic criteria and feedback from others. Analyze and evaluate impact of
choices made in the revision process.

1457F03BC42C4F7FBA3DFAD29FFA7201.description:
Choreograph a dance based on a selected theme. Articulate
the artistic intent, and analyze how the meaning drawn by the audiencemay
differ.

BABE73E249254FF1B6560031FFE0736D.description:
Choreograph a dance based on a selected theme and make
revisions to further develop the artistic intent.

0F01825E8FA9442D889F6E842ADBF7B0.description:
Choreograph a dance study that uses ideas and themes as
motivation. Explain how the movement is meant to represent the artistic
intent.

7EB2468B4E0D4A6FAB2DFEEC0171C079.description:
Choreograph a dance study that expresses and communicates
an idea or feeling. Discuss the effect of the movement choices.

A823DC2252DC4D6296EE208E0DDFD702.description:
Demonstrate mastery of choreographic devices, structures, and
processes. Express a personal voice in designing an original dancepiece.
Justify choreographic choices, and explain how they are used to enhance the
artistic intent.

3AD6B72FA5634B22BF53224780DBB9CA.description:
Demonstrate fluency of choreographic devices, structures, and
processes. Express a personal/collective voice in designing and
choreographing original dance compositions. Justify choreographic choices,
and explain how they are used to support artistry.

1A9669B79ABC4A54BC8406CB201788FF.description:
Design and implement a variety of choreographic devices and
dance structures to develop an original dance. Analyze how the structureand
final composition expresses the artistic intent.

0816113F09B947C89E1CC39161239234.description:
Design a dance study using choreographic devices and dance
structures to support an artistic intent. Explain how the dance structures
clarify the artistic intent.

017E551D72B547AC8C7576DF5E57BF0B.description: Organize and develop artistic ideas and work.

98D41323B2894FCC9580DE155C335ADA.description:
Expand personal movement preferences and strengths to
discover unexpected solutions that communicate the artistic intent of an
original dance. Analyze the solutions, and explain their effectiveness in
expanding artistic intent.

D798EAAABC9F42E087D6F6278F045EF2.description:
Apply personal movement preferences and strengths with the
movement vocabulary of two or more dance genres to choreograph original
dance studies or dances that communicate an artistic intent.

E96AC3AFF5E54BC2975C38C40EE1641B.description:
Apply personal movement preferences and strengths with the
movement vocabulary of a particular dance genre to choreograph anoriginal
dance study or dance that communicates an artistic intent.

F0769E51CE23470484CDBED61BAA9326.description:
Experiment with the elements of dance to explore personal
movement preferences and strengths, and select movements thatchallenge
skills and build on strengths in an original dance study or dance.

86F8102D51D94B88B30D5B28A92C8E8C.description:
Refine generated movement to develop a dance with clear
intent, purpose, or structure.

1F36051C80C94C12A6A30244F1956508.description:
Synthesize content generated from stimulus material.
Experiment and take risks to discover a personal voice to communicate
artistic intent.

E3D4EC51487A4574BBF3BCFB46248548.description:
Synthesize content generated from stimulus materials to
choreograph dance studies using original or codified movement.

A19F6A7FC68F4D68AD5FF431015CB35F.description:
Explore a variety of stimuli to generate movement through
improvisation. Develop self-awareness and self-confidence through the
exploration of movement. Analyze the process and the relationship between
the stimuli and the movement

A190B26D00C04F4E9AFF0B1A49D9C789.description: Generate and conceptualize artistic ideas and work.

73415A2F770D408F8FBE2BFC063619FD.description:
Work collaboratively to produce a dance concert, and design
and organize the production elements that would be necessary to fulfillthe
artistic intent of the dance works.

CCE1EBE0D35841BA8CFAD12E27623C67.description:
Work collaboratively to produce a dance piece/concert on a
stage or in an alternative performance venue, and plan the production
elements necessary to fulfill the artistic intent of the dance works.

3AF20067B9A34EC7999BA3B6D3954DD6.description:
Evaluate possible designs for the production elements of a
performance, and select and execute the ideas that would intensify and
heighten the artistic intent of the dances.

84B6FAFE7E424E2F86AD834F75C80CE9.description: Identify and analyze the basic elements of a danceproduction.

65BFEFC39A194F4D9C6676CAD973BA76.description:
Model performance etiquette and performance practices during
class, rehearsal, and performance. Implement performance strategies to
enhance projection. Accept notes from choreographer, and apply corrections to future rehearsals and performances. Document the rehearsal and
performance process, and evaluate methods and strategies using dance
terminology.

7E452FD702B94A86B1201556328FA56D.description:
Model performance etiquette and performance practices during
class, rehearsal, and performance. Implement performance strategies to
enhance projection. Accept notes from choreographer, and apply corrections
to future rehearsals and performances. Document the rehearsal and
performance process, and evaluate methods and strategies using dance
terminology.

B4679E8E185D474EA2A1D6BEBEC0A59D.description:
Demonstrate performance etiquette and performance practices
during class, rehearsal, and performance. Accept notes from choreographer,
and apply corrections to future rehearsals and performances.

0B06B494FEAB41AF8DC91C729502C325.description:
Identify performance etiquette and performance practicesduring
class, rehearsal, and performance.

9D91570FD4914C948ADB4299FC80B6DF.description: Express meaning through the performance of artistic work.

24BB230E143740349C75F2DA89B93ABD.description:
Plan and execute collaborative and independent practice to
achieve personal, technical, and artistic goals.

F2CF8E396733488C9CD2BE38E670E9FB.description:
Use a variety of strategies to analyze and evaluate rehearsals
and performances of self and others to achieve performance excellence (e.g.,
use video recordings for analysis).

685E28E5BEE247E0B1856D863EE44374.description:
Analyze and refine collaborative and independent practice to
achieve personal, technical, and artistic goals.

C9C6183667684DD585CBA1EA13CB4865.description:
Plan and execute collaborative and independent practice to
achieve personal, technical, and artistic goals.

89D9F791ADAA48389AB96C2B13476AF5.description:
Perform movement combinations in the center and across the
floor, demonstrating correct technique and musicality.

4911A3F0B0644044BE60C52FF3872D3F.description:
Incorporate healthful and safe practices for dancers, and modify
personal practices based on findings.

2EF3851776F64D07A05067E27F52A75E.description:
Apply and refine anatomical awareness and healthful practices
to technical dance skills to achieve fluency of movement and prevent injury.

46D463712BF44AAAAFBC3AB821F2EFCD.description:
Develop anatomical awareness and healthful practices to
technical dance skills to achieve fluency of movement and prevent injury.

DE0C9DAFB7CA43F4BFA8CAB78147B43D.description: Refine technique through teacher-directed corrections and selfevaluations using appropriate dance terminology.

0866F3AA08F54F70ACA1E7943C2264CF.description:
Apply technical and performance skills in complex choreography
when performing a solo, duet, or ensemble work in a variety of dance
genres.

2AF773BD55B142D196DCFF92BA443794.description:
Analyze and refine awareness of technical dance skills and
performance goals in two genres of dance. Technical dance skills include
proper body alignment, coordination, balance, core support, endurance,
transfer of weight, flexibility, and body part articulation in locomotor andaxial
movements.

1326080FD5AB424A8EB3390E27300C92.description:
Develop awareness through dancing with others by executing
complex spatial, rhythmic, and dynamic combinations to refine technical
dance skills previously learned and meet performance goals. Technicaldance
skills include proper body alignment, coordination, balance, core support,
endurance, transfer of weight, flexibility, and body part articulation in
locomotor and axial movements.

DEC1D5DA6A9E4D78A510B21B8DC8B54F.description:
Demonstrate technical dance skills including proper alignment,
coordination, balance, core support, endurance, transfer of weight, flexibility,
and body part articulation in locomotor and axial movements in a particular
genre.

79D755F0D7ED4EF1AE915D8CFEFCBC24.description: Develop and refine artistic techniques and work for performance.

8CB62A7785B14F34BAA063504E1D9E8E.description:
Modulate dynamics to clearly express intent while performing
phrases and choreography. Perform movement sequences expressively
using a broad dynamic range, and employ dynamic skills for establishing
relationships with other dancers and projecting to the audience.

B309BA7E84D94F2DA1D1A65DB3EAD4F2.description:
Develop total body awareness so that movement phrases
demonstrate variances of energy and dynamics by transitioning between
phrases.

453B3E04515F462AA56F0F3D0ADAACD1.description:
Connect energy and dynamics to movements by applying them
in and through all parts of the body.

C7F020DD3B1645B486825565F4553F7B.description:
Initiate movement phrases by applying energy and dynamics.
Vary energy and dynamics over the length of a phrase.

E0A3E22D8B0B4F4D86501B92D285B0DC.description:
Use multiple and complex rhythms (e.g., contrapuntal and/or
polyrhythmic) at the same time. Work with and against rhythm of
accompaniment or sound environments.

C0E72F27EAED4055AD4F14C2331EF0C0.description:
Modulate time factors for artistic interest, and express acuity.
Demonstrate time complexity in phrasing with and without musical
accompaniment.

D8C02B3397A9403DBEDCDA648F7614BE.description:
Perform dance studies and compositions that use time and
tempo in various ways. Use breath, internal rhythms, and kinetics asphrasing
tools.

8DBD3DFB4090485D92C1B2F66A90F805.description:
Use syncopation and accent movements related to different
tempi. Take rhythmic cues from different aspects of accompaniment.

B506B8EF74BD457D8123F20A6B29F7F4.description:
Identify and demonstrate movement for artistic andexpressive
clarity.

0BCC9E8D252545E8BBCC6A8CC0240662.description:
Understand inward and outward focus and demonstrate through
movement alone and with others.

9E58D3A038BB4B43BAD3D027CE0FEA76.description:
Execute combinations demonstrating level changes while
maintaining relationships through focus andintentionality.

455C65B47F934EE7A104A667E139D207.description:
Use space and levels intentionally during phrases andthrough
transitions alone and with others.

FC3FC6B95E92400A896D260DC77F9E91.description: Select, analyze, and interpret artistic work for performance.
